    <chapter xml:id="chap-solution-sets">
      <title>Solving Systems of Linear Equations</title>

      <introduction>
        <p>
          This chapter is devoted to solving systems of linear equations in a systematic way.
          <ul>
            <li>In <xref ref="systems-eqns"/> we begin with a brief discussion of systems of linear equations and their solutions.</li>
            <li>In <xref ref="vectors-matrices"/> we give an introduction to vector and matrix algebra, which will be used throughout the text.</li>
            <li>In <xref ref="elimination"/> we will learn the Gauss<ndash/>Jordan elimination algorithm, which is the fundamental tool for solving systems of equations.</li>
            <li>We turn to computational considerations in <xref ref="lu-decomposition"/>, where we will discuss how to use Gaussian elimination efficiently on a computer.</li>
            <li>In <xref ref="parametric-form"/> we will learn how to <em>parameterize</em> the solution set of a system of equations when the system has more than one solution.</li>
            <li>Finally, in <xref ref="spans"/> we will cover the geometric notion of <term>spans</term>, which we will use to <em>draw</em> the solution set of a system of equations.</li>
          </ul>
        </p>

      </introduction>

